<plan_depth_check>
Plan depth mode: {plan_depth from config}
{If plan_depth is "high-level":}
ADDITIONAL CHECK — Over-Specification Detection:
For each task's &lt;action&gt; block, flag as WARNING if it contains:
- Code keywords: const, let, function, class, interface, type, import, export
- Fenced code blocks (triple backticks)
- More than 8 numbered implementation steps
- Specific library API calls (e.g., X.method(), import X from Y)
Format: "WARNING: Over-specification in task {id}: &lt;action&gt; contains {pattern}. High-level mode expects deliverable descriptions, not implementation details."
These are WARNINGs, not BLOCKERs — the planner may have valid reasons for specificity.
{If plan_depth is "detailed":}
No over-specification check in detailed mode.
</plan_depth_check>

If all dimensions pass, return `## CHECK PASSED` with no issues block.

Do NOT write any files. Return your findings as your response text.
